<header>
	Look at the table and complete the sentences by choosing the correct word or phrase for each gap.  There is more than one correct answer in each case.
</header>
	
<section id="noscroll">
  <img class="leftFloat" src="../media/TT_AW_004a.jpg" mode="1" id="1003"/>
</section>

<section id="body">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000"><b>1</b>  Every year road transport consumed the greatest (&#x2026;) of petroleum.</font>
  </p>
  <g id="t21">A  quantity</g>
  <g id="t22">B  amount</g>
  <g id="t23">C  proportion</g>
  <g id="t24">D  number</g>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000"><b>2</b>  Petroleum consumption for railways was (&#x2026;) less than for other means of transport.</font>
  </p>
  <g id="t25">A  a lot</g>
  <g id="t26">B  far</g>
  <g id="t27">C  many</g>
  <g id="t28">D  much</g>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000"><b>3</b>  In 1999 road transport consumed (&#x2026;) petroleum than the previous year.</font>
  </p>
  <g id="t29">A  less</g>
  <g id="t30">B  fewer</g>
  <g id="t31">C  fewer tonnes of</g>
  <g id="t32">D  a smaller quantity of</g>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000"><b>4</b>  Petroleum consumption by air transport was (&#x2026;) in 1999 than ten years earlier.</font>
  </p>
  <g id="t33">A  many more</g>
  <g id="t34">B  much higher</g>
  <g id="t35">C  a lot higher</g>
  <g id="t36">D  far higher</g>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000"><b>5</b>  Over the years railway and water transport consumed (&#x2026;) petroleum.</font>
  </p>
  <g id="t37">A  less and less</g>
  <g id="t38">B  smaller and smaller amounts of</g>
  <g id="t39">C  fewer and fewer</g>
  <g id="t40">D  fewer and fewer tonnes of</g>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb24">
  <p align="left">1D. Petroleum is uncountable.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb27">
  <p align="left">2C. 'Many' is used for countable nouns, while 'less' is used for uncountable nouns. You cannot use the two together.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb30">
  <p align="left">3B. 'Few' and 'fewer' cannot be used with uncountable nouns such as 'petroleum'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb33">
  <p align="left">4A. The missing word refers to the noun 'consumption', which is uncountable.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb39">
  <p align="left">5C. Petroleum is uncountable. 'Fewer' can be used only with countable nouns.</p>
</section>

